    "Both approaches are further discussed in Sect. 7.",
    "Reinforcement learning provides a framework for learning and decision-making by trial and error (Sutton and Barto 2018).",
    "An RL Setting consists of four components (S, A, P, R) in a decision process.",
    "In this setting, an agent observes a state s ∈ S of the envi- ronment and, based on that, takes action a ∈ A, which results in a reward r = R(s, a), and the environment then transitions to a new state s � ∈ S.",
    "The interaction goes on in time steps until a terminal state is reached."
